# Git Rules

## Branch Strategy
- `main` → production. Never commit directly to main.
- `dev` → integration branch. Features merge here first.
- Feature branches off `dev`: `feature/short-description`
- Bug fixes: `fix/short-description`
- Chores (deps, config, refactor): `chore/short-description`

## Commit Messages
Follow conventional commits format:
```
type: short description (max 72 chars)
```

Types:
- `feat:` new feature
- `fix:` bug fix
- `chore:` maintenance, deps, config
- `refactor:` code change with no behavior change
- `style:` formatting, whitespace (not CSS)
- `docs:` documentation only

Examples:
```
feat: add user avatar upload
fix: correct overflow on mobile nav
chore: update shadcn button component
refactor: extract auth logic into useAuth hook
```

- Present tense, lowercase, no period at the end
- Be specific — "fix bug" is not a useful commit message

## Pull Requests
- PRs go from feature branch → `dev`, never directly to `main`
- PR title follows the same format as commit messages
- Keep PRs focused — one feature or fix per PR
- If a PR touches UI, include a screenshot or screen recording
- Squash commits when merging to keep history clean

## Worktrees (for parallel agent work)
When running multiple Claude agents simultaneously:
- Each agent creates its own worktree: `git worktree add ../project-feature-name feature/feature-name`
- Each agent works in its own isolated directory
- Each agent opens its own PR — never push to another agent's branch
- Clean up worktrees after merging: `git worktree remove ../project-feature-name`
